      "writtenOn": "2017-11-07T19:35:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Also, this doesn’t do what the comment says. You’re using lutimes() whenever Crashpad was built with a runtime OS minimum of less than 10.13. That code will still run on 10.13, and use this older lutimes() codepath.\n\nSomething like…\n\n#if defined(OS_POSIX)\n#if defined(OS_MACOSX) \u0026\u0026 MAC_OS_X_VERSION_MAX_ALLOWED \u003c MAC_OS_X_VERSION_10_13\n  static int (*const utimensat)(int, const char*, const timespec[2], int) \u003d [](){\n    Dl_info info;\n    if (!dladdr(utimes, \u0026info)) {\n      return nullptr;\n    }\n    void* dl_handle \u003d dlopen(info.dli_fname, RTLD_LAZY | RTLD_LOCAL | RTLD_NOLOAD);\n    if (!dl_handle) {\n      return nullptr;\n    }\n    return dlsym(dl_handle, \"utimensat\");\n  }();\n#endif\n  if (utimensat) {\n    // the contents of your current OS_POSIX branch\n    // you may need #pragma clang diagnostic push/ignored \"-Wunguarded-availability-new\"/pop\n  }\n#if defined(OS_MACOSX) \u0026\u0026 MAC_OS_X_VERSION_MIN_REQUIRED \u003c MAC_OS_X_VERSION_10_13\n  // the contents of your current OS_MACOSX branch\n#endif\n#endif  // OS_POSIX",
      "revId": "f06841bbc5d4435b2919e122d4c3df6b7653667c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f858dfad_fc8c150f",
        "filename": "test/filesystem.cc",
