      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-08T03:22:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, I thought I might need to do something like that, but was hesitant since it seems like a lot of complexity for test code when we don\u0027t expect to have sub-second precision in any tests anyways. What do you think of just always using lutimes() on MACOSX and leaving a comment about utimensat() being available in 10.13, should it ever be needed?",
      "parentUuid": "f660abda_7f8f26ad",
      "revId": "f06841bbc5d4435b2919e122d4c3df6b7653667c",
