      "writtenOn": "2017-11-07T19:35:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I see what you mean about the use of utimensat() vs. lutimes(), but this comment is confusing, because the resolution is also a property of the filesystem: HFS+ gives seconds, and APFS gives nanoseconds. APFS isn’t a possibility until 10.13, so really, you’re unlikely to get anything better than one-second resolution on, say, 10.12.",
      "revId": "f06841bbc5d4435b2919e122d4c3df6b7653667c",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
