      "message": "These are going to be flaky, because we can’t control scheduling, particularly on virtual machines. Even 2 seconds aren’t universally long enough.\n\nInstead of “now”, you can save a “before” and “after” time, and then make sure that the directory’s timestamp is between the two. You may still want to include the -2/+2 fudge factor to deal with uncertain filesystem timestamp resolution.",
